      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Yes, the trade-off this pull makes EDIT: is no longer made, thanks to review feedback. <strike>foregoing the optimization for a half dozen callers that don't already hold cs_main, in favor of avoiding re-taking the cs_main lock for the 18 callers that do already hold it, by moving the lock-taking to the half dozen callers (but just for the call itself, so essentially only the optimization is affected unless I am missing something).</strike>\r\n\r\nThanks for the link to #8007. It looks like the proportion of callers that hold the lock has since increased.",
